name: Billie Jean King Cup
summary: In the 2024 World Cup of Tennis, Canada's title defense was cut short in the quarter-finals by Great Britain. After severe weather forced the postponement of the opening match, Harriet Dart and Katie Boulter stunned Canada by winning their singles matches, while Emma Raducanu clinched victory in the doubles match alongside Dart. In other matches, Poland defeated host Spain thanks to Iga Swiatek's win, while Canada faced an uphill battle after Rebecca Marino's loss to Raducanu. The tournament began with Canada aiming to retain its Billie Jean King Cup title, but the competition proved to be fierce, ultimately ending their run in the quarter-finals.
